    "updated_at": "2023-03-20T23:31:45Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "After running 5 Besu clients on mainnet for several days I have found one peer failing the inbound handshake and succeeding to do a handshake at another time. That peer was a fork of geth on the ubiq chain(https://github.com/ubiq/go-ubiq). I checked the handshake code on that fork for differences to geth, but could not find any.\nChecking the IP addresses of clients that caused these failures have shown that a high percentage of these are located in China. This could point to software that uses the Ethereum discovery mechanism, but does not do the standard Ethereum handshake.",
